{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_012aAiyC35NineP5Gpdq77e6","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Story 11-2: sprint-status.yaml Becomes Derived View\n     2→\n     3→## Status: ready-for-dev\n     4→\n     5→## Story\n     6→\n     7→As a developer,\n     8→I want `sprint-status.yaml` generated from `sprint-state.json`,\n     9→So that there's one source of truth with a human-readable view.\n    10→\n    11→## Acceptance Criteria\n    12→\n    13→- [ ] AC1: Given `sprint-state.json` has story statuses, when `generateSprintStatusYaml()` is called, then it writes a valid YAML file matching the current sprint-status.yaml format <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    14→- [ ] AC2: Given a story status changes in `sprint-state.json`, when `writeSprintState()` completes, then `sprint-status.yaml` is regenerated automatically <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    15→- [ ] AC3: Given harness-run reads story statuses, when it queries state, then it reads from `sprint-state.json` directly (not sprint-status.yaml) <!-- verification: cli-verifiable -->\n    16→\n    17→## Technical Notes\n    18→\n    19→**Decision 1 (Unified State).** `sprint-status.yaml` transitions from source of truth to derived view. All readers must switch to `sprint-state.json`.\n    20→\n    21→Create `generateSprintStatusYaml()` function that:\n    22→1. Reads `sprint-state.json`\n    23→2. Transforms `stories` and `epics` into the current YAML format (epic groupings, story status lines)\n    24→3. Writes `sprint-status.yaml` using the same YAML structure that exists today\n    25→\n    26→Hook this into `writeSprintState()` so every state write auto-regenerates the YAML view. This ensures the human-readable file is always current without being a source of truth.\n    27→\n    28→Current readers of `sprint-status.yaml` that must switch to `sprint-state.json`:\n    29→- `src/lib/beads-sync.ts` — `readSprintStatus()` parses YAML to get story statuses\n    30→- `src/commands/status.ts` — reads sprint-status.yaml for display\n    31→- `src/commands/run.ts` — reads story statuses for selection\n    32→- `src/modules/sprint/selector.ts` — story selection reads statuses\n    33→- `src/modules/sprint/reporter.ts` — progress reporting\n    34→\n    35→The `readSprintStatus()` function in `src/lib/beads-sync.ts` should be replaced with direct reads from `sprint-state.json` via `readSprintState()`.\n    36→\n    37→The YAML generation can live in `src/lib/sync/sprint-yaml.ts` (anticipating Epic 12 restructuring) or temporarily in `src/modules/sprint/state.ts`.\n    38→\n    39→## Files to Change\n    40→\n    41→- `src/modules/sprint/state.ts` — Add `generateSprintStatusYaml()`, call it at end of `writeSprintState()`\n    42→- `src/lib/beads-sync.ts` — Replace `readSprintStatus()` YAML parsing with `readSprintState()` JSON reads\n    43→- `src/commands/status.ts` — Switch from sprint-status.yaml to sprint-state.json reads\n    44→- `src/commands/run.ts` — Switch status reads to sprint-state.json\n    45→- `src/modules/sprint/selector.ts` — Ensure story selection reads from sprint-state.json\n    46→- `src/modules/sprint/reporter.ts` — Switch progress reads to sprint-state.json\n    47→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01WHShw3WenWAwXLiDPJ4eCA","session_id":"bd5543f6-f408-4218-88bd-6e3bcdc37563","uuid":"af04bb5a-dbe3-4d68-a7bc-f69d8d192566","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:08:30.169Z"}
