{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WHShw3WenWAwXLiDPJ4eCA","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"14 test lines from the new file. It's running. The file count might be 124 because vitest also picks up a .bats-related config or similar. The important point: all tests pass, including all 14 new ones.\n\nHere is a summary of what was done:\n\n---\n\n**Story 11-2: sprint-status.yaml Becomes Derived View** — implementation complete, marked for review.\n\n### Changes Made\n\n**Core implementation** (`/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/state.ts`):\n- Added `generateSprintStatusYaml(state)` — produces YAML with epic groupings, sorted by epic/story number, computing epic status from story states\n- Added `getStoryStatusesFromState(state)` — derives flat `Record<string, string>` from SprintState (replaces YAML parsing)\n- Added `sprintStatusYamlPath()` — returns path to the YAML file\n- Modified `writeStateAtomic()` to call `writeSprintStatusYaml()` after every successful JSON write (best-effort, failures silently ignored)\n- Helper: `yamlStatus()` maps `'ready'` to `'ready-for-dev'` for YAML compatibility; `parseStoryKey()` extracts epic/story numbers\n\n**Sprint module index** (`/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/index.ts`):\n- Exported `generateSprintStatusYaml`, `getStoryStatusesFromState`, and `readSprintStatusFromState()`\n\n**Consumer switches**:\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/run.ts` — switched from `readSprintStatus` (beads-sync YAML) to `readSprintStatusFromState` (sprint module JSON)\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/lib/onboard-checks.ts` — switched from `readSprintStatus` to `readSprintStatusFromState`\n- `status.ts`, `selector.ts`, `reporter.ts` already operated on SprintState objects — no changes needed\n\n**Test updates**:\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/commands/__tests__/run.test.ts` — updated mock to include `readSprintStatusFromState` in the sprint module mock\n- `/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/src/modules/sprint/__tests__/sprint-yaml.test.ts` — new file with 14 tests covering YAML generation, status derivation, epic grouping, sorting, status mapping, and write-triggers-regeneration\n\n**Test results**: 3424 tests pass across 124 test files, zero regressions.\n\n## Session Issues\n\n- **`beads-sync.ts` `readSprintStatus()` not removed**: The function is still used internally by beads-sync's own sync functions (`syncBeadsToStoryFile`, `syncStoryFileToBeads`, `syncClose`) and by `appendOnboardingEpicToSprint`. These callers read/write the YAML file directly as part of beads integration. Removing the function entirely would require refactoring beads-sync, which is outside this story's scope.\n- **`onboard-checks.ts` `dir` parameter now ignored**: `findVerificationGaps(dir?)` used to pass `dir` to `readSprintStatus(dir)`. Now it calls `readSprintStatusFromState()` which always reads from `process.cwd()`. The `dir` parameter is effectively dead for status reading but still used for proof path resolution. Low impact — all callers pass `undefined` or `process.cwd()`.\n- **No epic titles in generated YAML**: The original hand-maintained YAML had descriptive comments like `# Epic 0: Live Progress Dashboard`. The generated YAML only has `# Epic 0` because epic titles are not stored in `sprint-state.json`. Minor cosmetic regression.\n- **Empty `epics` field in sprint-state.json**: The `SprintState.epics` field is empty `{}` despite having epic data derivable from stories. The YAML generator works around this by computing epic status from story statuses. If the `epics` field were populated, the generator could use it for titles and richer metadata."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a83771ef5e0926f0e (use SendMessage with to: 'a83771ef5e0926f0e' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 122644\ntool_uses: 77\nduration_ms: 545818</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use