{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01YVv4WW4rqbN6yedZU9H4xe","type":"tool_result","content":"The file /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md has been updated successfully."}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bd5543f6-f408-4218-88bd-6e3bcdc37563","uuid":"a97b8b8d-2fb4-4f85-87d7-0a34e6ef4b78","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:19:23.903Z","tool_use_result":{"filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/_bmad-output/implementation-artifacts/.session-issues.md","oldString":"- **CRITICAL: Dev agent corrupted sprint-state.json** — tests or writeStateAtomic() calls during dev overwrote the real sprint-state.json with a 2-story test fixture. Had to restore from ralph/.state-snapshot.json. The YAML auto-generation side effect in writeStateAtomic() is dangerous when called during tests.","newString":"- **CRITICAL: Dev agent corrupted sprint-state.json** — tests or writeStateAtomic() calls during dev overwrote the real sprint-state.json with a 2-story test fixture. Had to restore from ralph/.state-snapshot.json. The YAML auto-generation side effect in writeStateAtomic() is dangerous when called during tests.\n\n### 11-2-sprint-status-yaml-derived-view — code-review (2026-03-24T11:18Z)\n\n- HIGH (fixed): Test filesystem corruption — sprint-yaml.test.ts, state.test.ts, index.test.ts all wrote to real project dir. Converted to tmpdir isolation.\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Platform-incompatible path handling — used string slicing instead of dirname().\n- MEDIUM (fixed): Missing edge case tests — added 4 new tests for non-standard keys, empty dir, YAML write failures.\n- LOW (not fixed): run.ts still constructs sprintStatusPath for YAML in Ralph prompt.\n- LOW (not fixed): parseStoryKey not exported, yamlStatus has no exhaustiveness check.\n- **CRITICAL (PERSISTS): sprint-state.json and sprint-status.yaml corrupted AGAIN during code review despite tmpdir isolation fix.** Tests are still somehow writing to the real project directory. The test isolation is incomplete or some test path bypasses the tmpdir chdir.","originalFile":"# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24\n\n### 11-2-sprint-status-yaml-derived-view — dev-story (2026-03-24T11:10Z)\n\n- `beads-sync.ts` `readSprintStatus()` not removed — still used internally by beads-sync's own sync functions. Removing requires refactoring outside story scope.\n- `onboard-checks.ts` `dir` parameter now ignored for status reading — `readSprintStatusFromState()` always reads from `process.cwd()`. Low impact.\n- No epic titles in generated YAML — original had comments like `# Epic 0: Live Progress Dashboard`, generated only has `# Epic 0` since titles aren't in sprint-state.json.\n- Empty `epics` field in sprint-state.json — generator works around by computing epic status from story statuses.\n- **CRITICAL: Dev agent corrupted sprint-state.json** — tests or writeStateAtomic() calls during dev overwrote the real sprint-state.json with a 2-story test fixture. Had to restore from ralph/.state-snapshot.json. The YAML auto-generation side effect in writeStateAtomic() is dangerous when called during tests.\n","structuredPatch":[{"oldStart":7,"oldLines":3,"newStart":7,"newLines":12,"lines":[" - No epic titles in generated YAML — original had comments like `# Epic 0: Live Progress Dashboard`, generated only has `# Epic 0` since titles aren't in sprint-state.json."," - Empty `epics` field in sprint-state.json — generator works around by computing epic status from story statuses."," - **CRITICAL: Dev agent corrupted sprint-state.json** — tests or writeStateAtomic() calls during dev overwrote the real sprint-state.json with a 2-story test fixture. Had to restore from ralph/.state-snapshot.json. The YAML auto-generation side effect in writeStateAtomic() is dangerous when called during tests.","+","+### 11-2-sprint-status-yaml-derived-view — code-review (2026-03-24T11:18Z)","+","+- HIGH (fixed): Test filesystem corruption — sprint-yaml.test.ts, state.test.ts, index.test.ts all wrote to real project dir. Converted to tmpdir isolation.","+- MEDIUM (fixed): Platform-incompatible path handling — used string slicing instead of dirname().","+- MEDIUM (fixed): Missing edge case tests — added 4 new tests for non-standard keys, empty dir, YAML write failures.","+- LOW (not fixed): run.ts still constructs sprintStatusPath for YAML in Ralph prompt.","+- LOW (not fixed): parseStoryKey not exported, yamlStatus has no exhaustiveness check.","+- **CRITICAL (PERSISTS): sprint-state.json and sprint-status.yaml corrupted AGAIN during code review despite tmpdir isolation fix.** Tests are still somehow writing to the real project directory. The test isolation is incomplete or some test path bypasses the tmpdir chdir."]}],"userModified":false,"replaceAll":false}}
