{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01E8dhQyESVJr8kCt3buhCwj","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/11-2-sprint-status-yaml-derived-view-proof.md"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bd5543f6-f408-4218-88bd-6e3bcdc37563","uuid":"49d5ae82-dc37-4c13-b59a-3377675f0769","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:21:58.249Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/ivintik/dev/personal/codeharness/verification/11-2-sprint-status-yaml-derived-view-proof.md","content":"# Verification Proof: 11-2-sprint-status-yaml-derived-view\n\n**Story:** sprint-status.yaml Becomes Derived View\n**Verified:** 2026-03-24\n**Method:** unit-testable (all ACs cli-verifiable, no Docker needed)\n\n---\n\n## AC 1: generateSprintStatusYaml() produces valid YAML matching sprint-status.yaml format\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:**\n\n1. Function exists at `src/modules/sprint/state.ts:116`:\n   ```\n   export function generateSprintStatusYaml(state: SprintState): string {\n   ```\n\n2. 14 dedicated tests in `src/modules/sprint/__tests__/sprint-yaml.test.ts` verify:\n   - Valid YAML output (parseable by `yaml.parse()`)\n   - Epic groupings with `# Epic N` comments\n   - Stories sorted by epic number then story number\n   - Epic status computed from story statuses (done if all done, backlog otherwise)\n   - `ready` status mapped to `ready-for-dev` in YAML output\n   - Auto-generated header comment included\n   - Multiple epics with mixed statuses\n   - Non-standard keys handled gracefully\n   - Epics field populated but overridden by story-derived status\n\n3. All 3433 tests pass including all 14 new YAML generation tests.\n\n---\n\n## AC 2: writeSprintState() auto-regenerates sprint-status.yaml\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:**\n\n1. `writeSprintStatusYaml(state)` called at `src/modules/sprint/state.ts:204` inside `writeStateAtomic()`:\n   ```typescript\n   renameSync(tmp, final);\n   // Regenerate YAML view after successful state write\n   writeSprintStatusYaml(state);\n   ```\n\n2. Test \"writes sprint-status.yaml when directory exists\" verifies the file is created after `writeStateAtomic()`.\n\n3. Test \"YAML updates on every state write\" verifies that changing state from backlog→done produces updated YAML content.\n\n4. Test \"YAML write failure does not fail the state write\" verifies best-effort semantics.\n\n5. Test \"skips YAML write when output directory does not exist\" verifies graceful handling.\n\n---\n\n## AC 3: harness-run reads from sprint-state.json directly (not sprint-status.yaml)\n\n**Verdict:** PASS\n\n**Evidence:**\n\n1. `src/commands/run.ts` imports from sprint module (JSON-backed):\n   ```typescript\n   import { readSprintStatusFromState } from '../modules/sprint/index.js';\n   ```\n   Used at lines 67, 163, 205, 233, 259.\n\n2. `src/lib/onboard-checks.ts` also switched:\n   ```typescript\n   import { readSprintStatusFromState } from '../modules/sprint/index.js';\n   ```\n   Used at line 98.\n\n3. No remaining imports of `readSprintStatus` from `beads-sync.ts` in run.ts or onboard-checks.ts.\n\n4. `readSprintStatusFromState()` reads `sprint-state.json` via `readSprintState()` and extracts story statuses via `getStoryStatusesFromState()` — no YAML parsing involved.\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n| AC | Verdict |\n|----|---------|\n| AC1 | PASS |\n| AC2 | PASS |\n| AC3 | PASS |\n\n**All acceptance criteria verified. Story is complete.**\n\n## Known Issues\n\n- Test isolation: `writeStateAtomic()` side effect can corrupt real `sprint-state.json` and `sprint-status.yaml` when tests run without proper CWD isolation. Tests were converted to tmpdir isolation but the fix is fragile under parallel execution.\n- `beads-sync.ts` retains its own `readSprintStatus()` for internal use — not part of this story's scope.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
