{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01AGhrbebVyXs8t66jpjUgF7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# Session Issues Log — 2026-03-24\n     2→\n     3→### 11-2-sprint-status-yaml-derived-view — dev-story (2026-03-24T11:10Z)\n     4→\n     5→- `beads-sync.ts` `readSprintStatus()` not removed — still used internally by beads-sync's own sync functions. Removing requires refactoring outside story scope.\n     6→- `onboard-checks.ts` `dir` parameter now ignored for status reading — `readSprintStatusFromState()` always reads from `process.cwd()`. Low impact.\n     7→- No epic titles in generated YAML — original had comments like `# Epic 0: Live Progress Dashboard`, generated only has `# Epic 0` since titles aren't in sprint-state.json.\n     8→- Empty `epics` field in sprint-state.json — generator works around by computing epic status from story statuses.\n     9→- **CRITICAL: Dev agent corrupted sprint-state.json** — tests or writeStateAtomic() calls during dev overwrote the real sprint-state.json with a 2-story test fixture. Had to restore from ralph/.state-snapshot.json. The YAML auto-generation side effect in writeStateAtomic() is dangerous when called during tests.\n    10→\n    11→### 11-2-sprint-status-yaml-derived-view — code-review (2026-03-24T11:18Z)\n    12→\n    13→- HIGH (fixed): Test filesystem corruption — sprint-yaml.test.ts, state.test.ts, index.test.ts all wrote to real project dir. Converted to tmpdir isolation.\n    14→- MEDIUM (fixed): Platform-incompatible path handling — used string slicing instead of dirname().\n    15→- MEDIUM (fixed): Missing edge case tests — added 4 new tests for non-standard keys, empty dir, YAML write failures.\n    16→- LOW (not fixed): run.ts still constructs sprintStatusPath for YAML in Ralph prompt.\n    17→- LOW (not fixed): parseStoryKey not exported, yamlStatus has no exhaustiveness check.\n    18→- **CRITICAL (PERSISTS): sprint-state.json and sprint-status.yaml corrupted AGAIN during code review despite tmpdir isolation fix.** Tests are still somehow writing to the real project directory. The test isolation is incomplete or some test path bypasses the tmpdir chdir.\n    19→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01YXPK1TUxfRUPgh7Zdq99k3","session_id":"bd5543f6-f408-4218-88bd-6e3bcdc37563","uuid":"adb656cc-1215-4275-a79e-70dcb271839c","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:25:24.316Z"}
