{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JmB1RGVQbsx3DdQKy1YtMo","type":"tool_result","content":"   600→---\n   601→\n   602→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-24 (Sessions 14-15)\n   603→\n   604→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence (Architecture v3 Migration phase)\n   605→**Sessions:** 14 (Epic 10 completion + 10-5 dev) and 15 (11-1 create-story + dev-story)\n   606→**Session start:** ~10:12 UTC\n   607→**Session budget:** 30 minutes\n   608→**Appended:** 2026-03-24T14:12Z\n   609→\n   610→---\n   611→\n   612→## 1. Session Summary\n   613→\n   614→| Story | Epic | Outcome | Pipeline Stages Completed |\n   615→|-------|------|---------|---------------------------|\n   616→| 10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider | Epic 10 (Stack Provider Pattern) | done | dev-story, code-review, verification (completed earlier sessions for create-story) |\n   617→| Epic 10 retrospective | Epic 10 | done | retrospective run, epic marked done |\n   618→| 11-1-unified-sprintstate-schema-versioning | Epic 11 (Unified State) | review | create-story, dev-story completed |\n   619→\n   620→**Key events:**\n   621→- Epic 10 (Stack Provider Pattern) was fully completed -- all 5 stories done, retrospective run, epic marked done. Committed as `2974467` (10-5) and `97c24f5` (epic close).\n   622→- Story 11-1 progressed from backlog to review status. Both create-story (expanded to 19 ACs, 7 tasks) and dev-story stages completed. Still needs code review and verification.\n   623→- Sprint-status.yaml and session-issues.md were **overwritten by test data mid-session** and had to be restored from git. This caused disruption and data loss risk.\n   624→- No stories were fully completed to done status during this session's 30-minute window due to time constraints on 11-1.\n   625→\n   626→**Net progress:** Epic 10 closed (5/5 done). Epic 11 started -- 1 of 3 stories in review, 2 in backlog.\n   627→\n   628→---\n   629→\n   630→## 2. Issues Analysis\n   631→\n   632→### Category: Type System / Architecture\n   633→\n   634→| Severity | Source | Issue | Status |\n   635→|----------|--------|-------|--------|\n   636→| MEDIUM | epic-10 retro | CoverageToolName type fragmentation -- provider values don't match HarnessState strings | Tracked for Epic 14 |\n   637→| MEDIUM | 11-1 create-story | Circular dependency risk: retry-state.ts -> getSprintState() -> migrateFromOldFormat() potential cycle | Flagged, needs monitoring in dev |\n   638→\n   639→### Category: Story Scope / Planning\n   640→\n   641→| Severity | Source | Issue | Status |\n   642→|----------|--------|-------|--------|\n   643→| MEDIUM | epic-10 retro | Story 10-5 had 17 ACs and 8 consumer files -- heaviest story in the epic | Completed despite density |\n   644→| LOW | 11-1 create-story | Epic number reuse confusion -- previous sprint had a different Epic 11 (Retrospective Integration) | Documented, no action needed |\n   645→| LOW | 11-1 create-story | Stub overwrite -- existing 3-AC story file replaced with 19-AC, 7-task spec | Intentional improvement |\n   646→| LOW | 11-1 create-story | Deferred deletion of `.story_retries`/`.flagged_stories` to 11-3 to avoid data loss risk | Correct decision |\n   647→\n   648→### Category: Pre-existing Technical Debt\n   649→\n   650→| Severity | Source | Issue | Status |\n   651→|----------|--------|-------|--------|\n   652→| MEDIUM | epic-10 retro | Dispatch maps still enumerate all stacks explicitly, not caught by boundary test | Unresolved |\n   653→| HIGH | epic-10 retro, 11-1 dev | Pre-existing TS compilation errors (~87-100 lines across test files) persisted through Epics 8-10 | Unresolved, story 15-4 exists |\n   654→| LOW | 11-1 dev | `dir` parameter vestigial in retry-state.ts -- kept for backward compat but unused | Deliberate tech debt per spec |\n   655→\n   656→### Category: Test Infrastructure\n   657→\n   658→| Severity | Source | Issue | Status |\n   659→|----------|--------|-------|--------|\n   660→| LOW | 11-1 dev | Tests sharing project root's sprint-state.json interfere without full worker isolation | Pre-existing |\n   661→\n   662→### Category: Data Integrity / Operations\n   663→\n   664→| Severity | Source | Issue | Status |\n   665→|----------|--------|-------|--------|\n   666→| HIGH | session context | Sprint-status.yaml and session-issues.md overwritten by test data mid-session | Restored from git |\n   667→| INFO | 11-1 dev | Live sprint-state.json still v1 -- will auto-migrate to v2 on next getSprintState() call | Intended behavior |\n   668→\n   669→---\n   670→\n   671→## 3. What Went Well\n   672→\n   673→- **Epic 10 fully completed in a single day.** All 5 stories (10-1 through 10-5) went from backlog to done across sessions 8-15. The StackProvider pattern -- interface, registry, three providers, and consumer migration -- is fully landed.\n   674→- **Epic 10 retrospective was run.** The retrospective-then-close pattern was followed correctly.\n   675→- **Story 11-1 progressed quickly.** From backlog to review in one session, with create-story expanding the spec from 3 ACs to 19 ACs and dev-story completing the implementation. The schema versioning and migration logic is in place.\n   676→- **Correct architectural decisions in 11-1.** Deferring file deletion to 11-3 avoids data loss. Keeping the `dir` parameter for backward compat avoids breaking callers. Auto-migration on read is the right pattern.\n   677→- **Session issues log captured real problems.** The issues from the epic-10 retrospective and both 11-1 stages provide actionable input for future work.\n   678→\n   679→---\n   680→\n   681→## 4. What Went Wrong\n   682→\n   683→- **Sprint-status.yaml and session-issues.md overwritten by test data.** This is a serious operational problem. Test runs should never modify production state files. The files had to be restored from git, which means any updates written between the last commit and the overwrite were lost. Root cause: test isolation problem -- tests likely write to the project root instead of a temp directory.\n   684→- **No stories fully completed to done this session.** Story 11-1 reached review but still needs code review and verification. The 30-minute budget was consumed by epic-10 completion activities and 11-1 create+dev stages, leaving no time for review.\n   685→- **Pre-existing TS compilation errors remain chronic.** 87-100 errors across test files (bridge.test.ts, run.test.ts, teardown.test.ts, deps.test.ts, etc.) have persisted since Epic 8. Story 15-4 exists but remains in backlog with no scheduled date. This noise makes it harder to detect new errors introduced by changes.\n   686→- **sprint-state.json contains test data, not real sprint state.** The current file has generic `s1`-`s5` story keys with no relation to actual story IDs. This means the sprint-state.json is not being used as a reliable source of truth for sprint progress -- sprint-status.yaml is the actual record.\n   687→- **Circular dependency risk in 11-1 flagged but not yet validated.** The retry-state.ts -> getSprintState() -> migrateFromOldFormat() cycle was identified during create-story but whether the dev implementation avoids it has not been verified in code review.\n   688→\n   689→---\n   690→\n   691→## 5. Lessons Learned\n   692→\n   693→### Repeat\n   694→\n   695→- **Epic completion in a single day is achievable.** Epic 10 (5 stories) went from 0% to 100% in sessions 8-15. The key factors: consistent pipeline throughput (~1 story/session), clean provider pattern to follow, and thorough story specs.\n   696→- **Expanding story specs before development.** The 3-AC to 19-AC expansion for 11-1 gave the dev agent strong guidance. This pattern has been validated across every story in sessions 8-15.\n   697→- **Deferring risky operations (file deletion) to dedicated stories.** The decision to defer `.story_retries`/`.flagged_stories` deletion to 11-3 is correct -- it separates migration from cleanup and avoids data loss if migration is interrupted.\n   698→\n   699→### Avoid\n   700→\n   701→- **Tests writing to production state files.** The overwrite of sprint-status.yaml and session-issues.md by test data is unacceptable. Tests must use isolated temp directories. This should be a blocking fix before the next session.\n   702→- **Leaving sprint-state.json as test garbage.** The file currently contains meaningless `s1`-`s5` entries. Either reset it to a valid state or accept that sprint-status.yaml is the sole source of truth until story 11-2 (derived view) is implemented.\n   703→- **Accumulating TS compilation errors without remediation.** 87+ errors across 5+ test files is not \"noise\" -- it is a quality signal that has been ignored for 7+ sessions. Story 15-4 should be prioritized.\n   704→\n   705→---\n   706→\n   707→## 6. Action Items\n   708→\n   709→### Fix Now (Before Next Session)\n   710→\n   711→1. **Investigate and fix the test isolation problem.** Tests overwrote sprint-status.yaml and session-issues.md. Identify which test(s) write to the project root and fix them to use temp directories. This is a data integrity issue.\n   712→2. **Reset sprint-state.json to valid state or delete it.** The current `s1`-`s5` test data is misleading. Either restore it to reflect actual sprint state or acknowledge it as unused until 11-1 migration lands.\n   713→\n   714→### Fix Soon (Next Session)\n   715→\n   716→1. **Code review story 11-1.** The implementation is complete but unreviewed. Key areas to verify: circular dependency avoidance, migration correctness for `.story_retries` and `.flagged_stories` parsing, atomic write behavior, and backward compatibility of retry-state.ts public API.\n   717→2. **Verify story 11-1.** After review passes, run verification to move from review to done. All 19 ACs are `cli-verifiable`.\n   718→3. **Continue Epic 11.** Stories 11-2 (sprint-status.yaml derived view) and 11-3 (state reconciliation on session start) remain in backlog.\n   719→\n   720→### Backlog (Escalated Priority)\n   721→\n   722→1. **Story 15-4: Fix pre-existing TS compilation errors.** Escalate from backlog. 87+ errors across test files have persisted for 7+ sessions. This is now a chronic quality problem, not a minor annoyance.\n   723→2. **CoverageToolName type fragmentation (Epic 14).** Provider values vs HarnessState strings mismatch blocks clean provider adoption in coverage.ts.\n   724→3. **Dispatch maps explicit stack enumeration.** Not caught by the 10-5 boundary test. Needs a follow-up story or addition to 14-x.\n   725→\n   726→### Backlog (Carry Forward)\n   727→\n   728→All items from sessions 8-13 backlog remain open: 15-2/15-5 lint rules, StackDetection dedup, double detection in recoverCorruptedState, `_resetRegistry` export cleanup, readTextSafe catch branch, registry.ts 94.73% coverage, hasPythonDep normalization, TOML regex replacement, proof parser docs, installOtlp integration tests, comment-matching in dependency detection.\n   729→\n   730→---\n   731→\n   732→## Cross-Session Summary (Sessions 8-15, 2026-03-24)\n   733→\n   734→### Stories completed today: 5\n   735→- **10-1-stackprovider-interface-and-registry** -- done (session 8)\n   736→- **10-2-nodejs-provider** -- done (session 9)\n   737→- **10-3-python-provider** -- done (sessions 10-11)\n   738→- **10-4-rust-provider** -- done (sessions 12-13)\n   739→- **10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider** -- done (sessions 13-14)\n   740→\n   741→### Epics completed today: 1\n   742→- **Epic 10: Stack Provider Pattern** -- done (all 5 stories, retrospective, marked done)\n   743→\n   744→### Stories in progress: 1\n   745→- **11-1-unified-sprintstate-schema-versioning** -- review (create-story + dev-story done, needs code review + verification)\n   746→\n   747→### Cumulative stats\n   748→- Tests: 3098 -> 3397+ (299+ new tests, exact count post-10-5 and 11-1 not confirmed)\n   749→- Bugs caught by code review: 17+ (across sessions 8-14)\n   750→- Bugs shipped: 0\n   751→- Stories blocked: 0\n   752→- Epics completed: 1 (Epic 10)\n   753→- Tech debt items deferred: 11+ (carried forward from prior sessions, plus new items from 11-1)\n   754→- Operational incidents: 1 (test data overwriting production state files)\n   755→\n   756→### Sprint velocity\n   757→- Epic 10 progress: 0/5 -> 5/5 in one day (8 sessions)\n   758→- Epic 11 progress: 0/3 -> 0/3 done, 1/3 in review\n   759→- Pipeline throughput: ~1 story per ralph session (consistent)\n   760→- Session 14-15 effective throughput: 1 story completed (10-5) + 1 story to review (11-1) + 1 epic closed\n   761→\n   762→---\n   763→\n   764→# Session Retrospective — 2026-03-24 (Sessions 16-17)\n   765→\n   766→**Sprint:** Operational Excellence (Architecture v3 Migration phase)\n   767→**Sessions:** 16 (11-1 code review + epic 10 closeout), 17 (11-1 continued work, currently running)\n   768→**Session start:** ~13:11 UTC (ralph loop restart)\n   769→**Appended:** 2026-03-24T14:57Z\n   770→\n   771→---\n   772→\n   773→## 1. Session Summary\n   774→\n   775→| Story | Epic | Outcome | Pipeline Stages Completed |\n   776→|-------|------|---------|---------------------------|\n   777→| 10-5-migrate-consumers-to-stackprovider | Epic 10 (Stack Provider Pattern) | done (committed in prior sessions, verified in this ralph loop iter 1) | verification completed |\n   778→| 11-1-unified-sprintstate-schema-versioning | Epic 11 (Unified State) | verifying (code review done, implementation committed, in verification loop) | code-review completed, dev fixes applied |\n   779→\n   780→**Key events:**\n   781→- Ralph restarted a new loop at ~13:11Z with 44/66 stories done.\n   782→- **Iteration 1 timed out (30m).** Was working on 10-5 closeout and session retro. State delta: 10-4 moved from `backlog` to `verifying`.\n   783→- **Iteration 2 timed out (30m).** Was working on 11-1. State delta: 10-4 moved to `done`, 10-5 moved from `backlog` to `verifying`.\n   784→- **Iteration 3 completed successfully (~25m).** Completed 11-1 code review. Story moved to `review` status. Session issues log updated with 7 findings from code review.\n   785→- **Iteration 4 currently running** (~14:38Z start). Working on 11-1 next pipeline stage.\n   786→- Two timeout reports generated: `timeout-report-1-unknown.md` and `timeout-report-2-unknown.md`. Both show the agent was writing session retro content when time expired -- a recurring pattern of retro-writing consuming excessive time.\n   787→\n   788→**Net progress:** Epic 10 fully closed (was already done, now verified in state). Story 11-1 advanced from `review` to `verifying`. Sprint at 44/66 done.\n   789→\n   790→---\n   791→\n   792→## 2. Issues Analysis\n   793→\n   794→### Bugs Discovered During Implementation or Verification\n   795→\n   796→| Severity | Story | Issue | Fixed? |\n   797→|----------|-------|-------|--------|\n   798→| MEDIUM | 11-1 | `parseStoryRetriesRecord` accepted negative retry counts | Yes (code review fix) |\n   799→| MEDIUM | 11-1 | `parseFlaggedStoriesList` allowed duplicate entries | Yes (code review fix) |"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_01YXPK1TUxfRUPgh7Zdq99k3","session_id":"bd5543f6-f408-4218-88bd-6e3bcdc37563","uuid":"19495fc4-8967-4bf7-808f-3da0f345cd33","timestamp":"2026-03-24T11:26:35.943Z"}
